<br>
The last 2 (maybe 3 can't remember) raids we tried West Camp breaks and it ended in disaster 4-6 hour CR inwhich ended up only to be saved by two other guilds. (Valoran and Eternal Wrath) This break was a lot quicker and less frustrating than the other ones. I would recommend doing a north camp break this way again anytime. If we had more clerics we probably would have gotten one camped the first try in and been ready to go right away. <br>
<br>
Or another option which Zellex and I talked about was that we camp a cleric in Fear the night before the raid. Then all we have to do is make sure that everyone makes it to the Firewall before they die. We could use this strategy for Hate also.<br>
<br>
All in all I had a blast though. Better loot would have been nice. And ya I did get a kick out of lottoing off Nightmare Hides. The warts didn't surprise me though every time I go those are lottoed off. :P<br>
